From: LineageOS Desktop Project <noreply@local>
Subject: [PATCH] Launcher3: enable deep shortcuts in the taskbar long-press popup

Patch summary:
Upstream TaskbarPopupController forces deepShortcutCount to 0 whenever the
long-pressed icon is displayed in the taskbar (DISPLAY_TASKBAR), suppressing
app-declared deep shortcuts such as Chromium's "New tab" / "New incognito tab"
in the taskbar context menu. The accompanying upstream TODO (b/198438631)
acknowledges the stub.

The data path actually works end-to-end through TaskbarActivityContext:

- mContext.getActivityComponent().getPopupDataProvider() returns the same
  singleton PopupDataProvider that the workspace popup uses; the deep shortcut
  count is read from BgDataModel.deepShortcutMap, which is populated by the
  launcher model regardless of which context is asking.
- PopupContainerWithArrow.populateAndShowRows() -> addDeepShortcuts() only
  needs a DeviceProfile, a DragController, and an itemOnClickListener from
  the activity context. TaskbarActivityContext provides working implementations
  for all three (itemOnClickListener bound to onTaskbarIconClicked).
- The downstream PopupPopulator + ShortcutRequest.query() + IconCache lookups
  are identical to the workspace-icon code path; only updateIconUi=false at
  the create site differs.

Removing the isTaskbarIcon gate is therefore sufficient to surface the deep
shortcuts in the taskbar popup, with rendering and click-to-launch handled
by code that is already present and wired.

Kept separate from packages-apps-Launcher3.patch and the dynamic-display /
visual-effects supplementaries so this single-hunk fix can be reverted in
isolation if an upstream rebase changes the taskbar popup flow.

Applies on top of packages-apps-Launcher3.patch.

diff --git a/quickstep/src/com/android/launcher3/taskbar/TaskbarPopupController.java b/quickstep/src/com/android/launcher3/taskbar/TaskbarPopupController.java
index f20c4cbddc..1a1a1a1a1a 100644
--- a/quickstep/src/com/android/launcher3/taskbar/TaskbarPopupController.java
+++ b/quickstep/src/com/android/launcher3/taskbar/TaskbarPopupController.java
@@ -228,9 +228,8 @@ public class TaskbarPopupController implements TaskbarControllers.LoggableTaskba
         mContext.onTaskbarPopupOpening();
 
         PopupContainerWithArrow<BaseTaskbarContext> container;
-        boolean isTaskbarIcon = icon.getIconDisplay() == BubbleTextView.DISPLAY_TASKBAR;
-        int deepShortcutCount = isTaskbarIcon ? 0 : mContext.getActivityComponent()
-                .getPopupDataProvider().getShortcutCountForItem(itemInfo);
+        int deepShortcutCount = mContext.getActivityComponent()
+                .getPopupDataProvider().getShortcutCountForItem(itemInfo);
         // TODO(b/198438631): add support for INSTALL shortcut factory
         final ItemInfo finalInfo = itemInfo;
         List<SystemShortcut<BaseTaskbarContext>> systemShortcuts = getSystemShortcuts()
